f=Cybersecurity/keyring/custom/access-reviews/SKILL.md · in=periodic check everyone still needs access they catching privilege creep, orphaned accounts, over-grants JML discipline misses over time. Reviews follow **Hack23 access-control-policy** framework (6-tier asset classification monthly/quarterly/semi-annual/annual review cadences, 90-day dormant account detection threshold), automated baseline-vs-actual diffing `scripts/access_review.py`. identity's actual entitlements compared against least-privilege baseline their role, excess flagged operator revoke (revoke-then-appeal). **Review methodology sourced from:** Hack23 access-control-policy (6-tier review cadences, dormant account detection, break-glass post-review). **Automated diff:** custom access_review.py. · p=Access ever accumulates without reviews: people change projects, keep old access, years later everyone touch everything. Recertification resets least privilege cadence "does person still need this?" question, asked regularly, cheapest breach-blast-radius reducer is. · wu=review cadence fires (per Hack23 matrix: **monthly** RESTRICTED/Cloud Infra/Financial Systems, **quarterly** Development, **semi-annual** BI, **annual** Marketing)., After reorg major role changes (bulk creep)., high-privilege set needs recertification (monthly Hack23 matrix)., Dormant account sweep (90+ days activity Hack23 threshold). · st:/ Protocol=`REVIEW SCOPE (per Hack23 cadence: which asset tiers due this cycle) \· → BASELINE (per role, least-privilege entitlement set from identity-lifecycle's role access sets) \· → COMPARE (each identity's actual entitlements vs role baseline — scripts/access_review.py diffs) \· → OVER-GRANTS (actual minus baseline → revoke) \· → ORPHANS (accounts with no role → flag to warden)` · h3:Phase Scope (Hack23 cadence)=**Determine which asset tiers due review.** Hack23 access control matrix: · h3:Phase Scope (Hack23 cadence)=**Monthly**: RESTRICTED Data, Cloud Infrastructure, Financial Systems, **Quarterly**: Development Platforms, **Semi-Annual**: Business Intelligence, **Annual**: Marketing Platforms · h3:Phase Scope (Hack23 cadence)=**Check dormant accounts.** Hack23, accounts authentication activity 90+ days flagged dormant. disabled after notification never left active. · h3:Phase Diff (Custom Script)=**Baseline first.** review needs least-privilege baseline role compare against; without you're re-approving whatever exists. baseline comes identity-lifecycle's role access sets. **Diff, don't eyeball.** `access_review.py` computes actual-minus-baseline (over-grants), baseline-minus-actual (under-grants, rare), orphans (accounts role), dormant flags (90-day threshold) reviews complete repeatable, spot-check. · h3:Phase 3 — Recertify=**Revoke-then-appeal.** grant owner justify removed default; burden keeping access, removing (Fleet Charter Rail 2's doctrine agents, applied people). "Might need someday" justification. **Break-glass events reviewed.** Hack23 practice, any break-glass use since last review post-reviewed necessary? logged? avoided? · h3:Phase 4 — Report=**keyring diffs recommends; operator revokes.** security-inversion keyring produces review revocation list; operator/IdP executes. **Systemic creep risk.** reviews keep finding over-grants, role baseline wrong JML slipping surfaced warden's register, re-revoked cycle. · of=`## Access Review: [scope] — [date] \· Asset tiers reviewed: [per Hack23 matrix] \· Cadence: [monthly/quarterly/etc.] \· Baseline source: [role access sets] \· Reviewed: [n identities] \· Over-grants (revoke): [identity \· entitlement \· no-justification] → operator \· Orphans / role-mismatches: [flags → warden register]` · pr=**Hack23 cadences** review frequency tied asset classification; monthly critical, annual low-risk., **Baseline-driven** compare least-privilege, status quo., **Diff, don't eyeball** script-computed, complete, repeatable., **Revoke-then-appeal** burden keeping access., **Dormant disabled** 90-day threshold;